<h3 id="overview">Overview</h3>
<p>
    <code>CustomPositioner</code> is the single contract every positioning provider implements. Its one method,
    <code>position()</code>, places a floating element relative to an anchor and returns a <em>cleanup</em>
    function that tears down any listeners (used by <code>tracking: 'follow'</code>). The native-first default
    provider and every library adapter (<a href="/adapters/floating-ui-adapter/">Floating UI</a>, …) satisfy
    this same interface, which is what lets <a href="/plugs/custompositioningregistry/">the registry</a> treat
    them interchangeably.
</p>

<h3 id="standards">Web Standards Alignment</h3>
